%N A181534 Minimum number of rounds to be played to decide a two-player game of up to n rounds in which the winner of round j receives j points.
%C A181534 The game described above is played in the German TV Show 'Schlag den Raab'.
%C A181534 a(n) is the least k such that 2*A000217(k) > A000217(n). - _Peter Kagey_, Nov 07 2016
%H A181534 Peter Kagey, <a href="/A181534/b181534.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A181534 For n = 15, the maximum number of rounds per game in the show, a(n) = 11. So there are at least eleven rounds to be played in each game.
%t A181534 Table[ Ceiling[ -1/2 + Sqrt[1/4 + 2 Ceiling[(n^2 + n + 2)/4]]], {n, 1, 50} ]
%o A181534 (PARI) a(n)=ceil(sqrt((n^2 + n + 5)\4*2+1/4)-1/2) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jun 19 2013
